#inline#mFMb_DS_GetAlarm( { idleMode } )/*	What it does:	It returns True or False, depending if an alarm is set for the optional idle mode		Required parameters:	none, it wil get the alarm boolean for userNotIdle if no parameter is given		Optional parameters:	"userIdle", "userNotIdle", "scriptPaused", "scriptRunning" or "unSafe"		returns:	True or False or evaluation error 1224		( could return error number 7 in mFMb_GetErrNum afterwards)		notes:	For more information, see the example file "Idle Modes".		see also:	mFMb_DS_SetAlarm( boolean {; idleMode } )*/